Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the theoretical foundation of blockchains, which is closely related to cryptography and security. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an axiomatically constructed blockchain group, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the internal properties of blockchains under algebraic groups, which can be analyzed using information theory. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to social and information networks as blockchain systems are often used in decentralized networks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve computational complexity analysis of the blockchain group and its properties.
